description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/15859/documentation

This global dataset is a copy of the regional CH dataset, except for the following modifications.;The production volume represents the global annual production.;The geographicalCorrelation score of every pedigree matrix of was changed to '5'.;The comments below were part of the CH regional dataset.;This dataset represents the production of 1 tree cultivated after planting during 3 years of establishment phase. Not included are trellis systems of the orchard such as posts or wires to attach trees. The input are related to an orchard of 1 ha and 2000 trees.;This dataset refers to an average situation; for specific situations exchanges might differ substantially due to site specific parameters.

This activity starts with tillage (plough), soil cultivation, grass sowing between tree rows, and fertiliser and pesticide application during the period of the first three years.

This activity ends with an established orchard, three years after planting, that is at the beginning of the productive phase, i.e. the years in which the yield is of economic significance.

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Time period referring to the data source: 2011. Based on expert opinion data is considered to be valid at least up to 2015.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The amount of the exchanges are copy from a regional dataset.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Inputs for fertilisers and pesticides and related machinery work processes are taken from ecoinvent v2.2 activity: 'Apple, IP, at farm/kg/CH U' that represent 1 year in the productive phase of an apple orchard. These data were adapted to the establishment phase of an orchard as follows: The reference flow is 0.00075 of 1 year in the productive phase; the factor 0.00075 is based on the assumption that in one year of the establishment phase uses 0.5 of the inputs of a productive year, the establishment phase lasts for 3 years and 2000 trees per ha are planted in the orchard (1 * 0.5 * 3 / 2000 = 0.00075).
